<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217426>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17 – 21. Multidentorhodacarus triramulus (Karg, 1998). Female (based on Colombian specimens). 17. Chelicera; 18. Epistome; 19. Hypostome and basal palp segments; 20. Dorsal idiosomal shields; 21. Ventral idiosoma. Lyrifissures are represented by circles or ovals enclosing a dot. Lyrifissures enlarged for improved visibility." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217426/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

